This file describes my emacs setup.

The configuration currently has the following layout:

~/.emacs.d/:
init.el
init/keyb.el          - keyboard bindings
init/lang.el          - language support
init/linux.el         - Linux specifice options
init/modeline.el      - modeline customisation
init/org.el           - org-mode setup
init/osx.el           - OS X specific options
init/settings.el      - general settings
init/ui.el            - UI specific options
init/vc.el            - version control options
init/windows.el       - Windows specific options

site-lisp/magit       - Submodule linking to https://github.com/magit/magit.git
site-lisp/nxhtml      - Submodule linking to https://github.com/emacsmirror/nxhtml.git
site-lisp/org-mode    - Submodule linking to git://orgmode.org/org-mode.git
site-lisp/python-mode - Submodule linking to https://github.com/emacsmirror/python-mode.git
site-lisp/slime       - Submodule linking to https://github.com/emacsmirror/slime.git
site-lisp/tramp       - Submodule linking to https://github.com/emacsmirror/tramp.git
site-lisp/zenburn     - Submodule linking to https://github.com/dbrock/zenburn-el.git

The file ~/.emacs.d/init.el replaces ~/.emacs - emacs looks in both
these locations for its initialisation file.
